<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h2>Handling Events</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-4 form-group">
        {{#twbs-span
                onHide=(action "fireEvent" "#js-hide")
                onHidden=(action "fireEvent" "#js-hidden")
                onInserted=(action "fireEvent" "#js-inserted")
                onShow=(action "fireEvent" "#js-show")
                onShown=(action "fireEvent" "#js-shown")
                title="As events fire their corresponding label will color green-orange-red."}}
          Hover over this for a demonstration of the tooltip events firing.
        {{/twbs-span}}
        <p>
          <span class="label label-default" id="js-inserted">Inserted</span>
          <span class="label label-default" id="js-show">Show</span>
          <span class="label label-default" id="js-shown">Shown</span>
          <span class="label label-default" id="js-hide">Hide</span>
          <span class="label label-default" id="js-hidden">Hidden</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-8">
        {{!-- @formatter:off --}}
<pre>\{{#twbs-span
  onHide=(action "fireEvent" "#js-hide")
  onHidden=(action "fireEvent" "#js-hidden")
  onInserted=(action "fireEvent" "#js-inserted")
  onShow=(action "fireEvent" "#js-show")
  onShown=(action "fireEvent" "#js-shown")
  title="Watch all the events."}}
  Hover over this for a demonstration of the tooltip events firing.
\{{/twbs-span}}
&lt;p>
  &lt;span class="label label-default" id="js-inserted">Inserted&lt;/span>
  &lt;span class="label label-default" id="js-show">Show&lt;/span>
  &lt;span class="label label-default" id="js-shown">Shown&lt;/span>
  &lt;span class="label label-default" id="js-hide">Hide&lt;/span>
  &lt;span class="label label-default" id="js-hidden">Hidden&lt;/span>
&lt;/p>
</pre>
        {{!-- @formatter:on --}}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-info">
      <p><strong>Some Things To Understand About Tooltip Events</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          You can supply actions to the <code>onHide</code>, <code>onHidden</code>,
          <code>onInserted</code>, <code>onShow</code>, and <code>onShown</code> attributes of
          your component.
        </li>
        <li>
          Each one of the actions you specify will be default come with two arguments; the first
          is the JQuery wrapped element and the second the reference to the component itself. If
          you send any extra arguments to your action they will come before the element and
          component arguments.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

